# Bash scripts in this repo

Apply when editing files under `scripts/`.

## Required

- Shebang: `#!/bin/bash` (first line)
- Double-quote all variable and command substitutions: `"$name"`, `"$1"`, `"$(date)"`
- One concept per script; match naming and style of neighbors (e.g. `bestdayever_v2.sh`)

## Arguments

```bash
# One combined value (full name from multiple words)
name="$*"

# Separate parameters
greeting="$1"
name="$2"
```

## Patterns used in this repo

```bash
# Variable
name="John"
echo "Hello, $name"

# Read input
read -p "What is your name? " name

# Arithmetic
sum=$((num1 + num2))

# Command substitution
echo "Today is $(date +%Y-%m-%d)"
```

## Avoid

- `#!/usr/bin/zsh` or other non-bash shebangs
- Unquoted `$var`, `$1`, `$*`
- Legacy backticks; use `$(...)`
- Over-engineering: functions, strict mode, or error frameworks unless the lesson requires it
- Changing unrelated scripts when editing one file

When adding a script, add a linked section in `notes.md`. Put recurring Q&A in `faq.md`, not inline essays in the script.
